com.xilinx.rapidwright.util

Class ParallelismTools

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.util.ParallelismTools

  • public class ParallelismTools
extends Object
    Utilities to aid in parallel processing A class that abstracts away single-threaded and multi-threaded execution. Single-threaded mode means that all tasks submitted will be executed immediately (on the submitting thread).

        Type Parameters:

      • joinFirst

        public static <T> T joinFirst(Deque<Future<T>> futures)
        For a given Deque of Futures, block until the first is complete and remove it from the deque. First, try and steal the task from the queue and execute it on this thread. If this is not possible (indicating another thread may already be working on it) then use this thread productively by trying to steal the next task to work on.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type returned by all tasks.
        Parameters:
        futures - A Deque of Future objects corresponding to previously submitted tasks.
        Returns:
        The value returned by the first task.

      • join

        public static <T> void join(List<Future<T>> futures)
        For a given List of Futures, block until all are complete. The list is walked in reverse order and tasks are stolen from the queue so that they may be completed using the current thread.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type returned by all tasks.
        Parameters:
        futures - A List of Future objects corresponding to previously submitted tasks.
